<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>creation of files (or directories) are permit in the directory specified by php.ini directive "upload_tmp_dir" but write on directory is forbidden (rename, move, delete)</p>

<p>Zend_File_Transfer_Adapter_Abstract use internal method _isPathWriteable() to check if a file can be created in its method _getTmpDir().</p>

<p>After tmpDir is defined, method setDestination() is called and it's simply a call to php function is_writable that return false in our case (so exception is thrown)</p>

<p>Why not use the same method - _isPathWriteable() which create a test file - to check if a file can be wrote in directory ?</p>

<p>context:
zend framework: 1.12.0 (but seems exists in 1.12.3)
php 5.4.0
os: windows server 2008</p>

